thread.title: SEC Power Rankings: Week 6

author: courier-journal.com
title: SEC Power Rankings: Week 6
text:
LEXINGTON, Ky. – There’s a new No. 1 team in The Courier-Journal’s Southeastern Conference power rankings after Florida’s upset win over Ole Miss.
Alabama’s blowout of Georgia also has shaken up the top of the rankings with LSU taking over the No. 1 spot and the Crimson Tide slide in at No. 2. Texas A&M is still battling for top honors after taking down Mississippi State. Florida’s 38-10 win against the Rebels has the Gators rounding out the top four.
Alabama will look to stay on track when it welcomes Arkansas to Bryant-Denny Stadium (7 p.m. on ESPN), but the league’s other marquee matchups Saturday are in the East. Georgia will travel to Tennessee (3:30 p.m. on CBS), and Florida will travel to Missouri (7:30 p.m. on the SEC Network). The lone cross-divisional matchup is LSU at South Carolina (noon on ESPN).
Mississippi State and Ole Miss host non-conference opponents this week while Kentucky, Auburn, Texas A&M and Vanderbilt are all off Saturday.
